Install Screenlyapp On Raspberry-PI
=========================================

==------------------
  Requirements  - http://www.screenlyapp.com/ose.html
=============

Before you begin, you need to make sure you have the following:
--------------------------------------------------------------
   - A Raspberry Pi (Model B).
   - An SD Card (>4GB). Class 10 is highly recommended.
   - An HDMI-cable.
   - A network connection (with DHCP).
   - A keyboard (only required for the installation).
   - A monitor/TV that can view full HD (and has HDMI input).


1.Download Image from Source
	

Download the custom image: http://releases.screenlyapp.com/2013-11-18-Screenly_OSE_4GB.zip


2. Boot image to SD CARD 
  --  We recommend that you use Win32 Disk Imager to do this. The process is straight forward.

3.After booting,once demo video completes press
	CTRL+ALT+1

4.LOGIN WITH
		user 'pi' and the password 'raspberry'
5.sudo raspi-config
6.you must restart your Raspberry Pi
7.changes and rebooted, open a terminal (ctrl+alt+F1)

== login as a PI user 

8.curl -sL https://raw.github.com/wireload/screenly-ose/master/misc/install.sh | bash



{ reboot your system}  

Browse for ::  http://localhost:8080). 
